Nigerian football manager, Coach Augustine Eguavoen, has disclosed how he fired up the Super Eagles players to focus on the game and perform excellently well in the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations. Eguavoen revealed this while speaking to reporters during his post-match conference, stating that he encouraged the boys “you don’t have any other country to play for, it’s only Nigeria and you know how passionate our people are when it comes to football.” He further expressed how happy he is that people are starting to respect Nigeria, prior to when they started the game when everyone wrote Nigeria. Stop Calling Eguavoen ‘Local’ Coach, Actor Deyemi Warns Reno… AFCON: My Goal Against Guinea Bissau Means A Lot To Me, My… “For the first game, nobody gave us a chance but we did the job collectively. “And then, that game was gone. We had to put it behind us and then focus on the next game. Went ahead to beat Sudan and then put it behind us and then focus on the next game. “Now, people are thinking and starting to respect Nigeria,” he said.